# Offline InfoSys Lookup (MSHC)

## Search Priority

**Always offline first, online only as fallback.**

1. `twincat_infosys_mshc_search` (offline, structured, fast)
2. Only if offline returns 0 results → `twincat3-infosys-lookup` skill (web)

## How to Search

### Known type name → default (auto mode)

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="FB_IotMqttClient")
```

`auto_read=true` (default) includes full page content on exact match. One call is enough.

### Unknown name, know the concept → fulltext mode (BM25)

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="read Modbus input registers", mode="fulltext")
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="send email SMTP", mode="fulltext")
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="PID controller", mode="fulltext")
```

FTS5 BM25 ranking finds pages containing ALL query words regardless of order.

### Partial name → prefix search

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="FB_Json*", mode="fulltext")
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="FB_MB*", mode="fulltext")
```

### Exact phrase → quote the phrase

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="\"input registers\"", mode="fulltext")
```

### Only typed symbols (no articles) → symbol mode

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="MQTT", mode="symbol")
```

## Search Strategy for Unknown Types

1. Try the most specific query first (exact name if known)
2. If 0 results: broaden to description keywords in fulltext mode
3. If 0 results: try prefix search with type prefix (`FB_*`, `ST_*`, `E_*`)
4. If still 0 results: fall back to online InfoSys (`twincat3-infosys-lookup` skill)

## Fulltext Performance

- Title/symbol search: <1ms (in-memory)
- BM25 fulltext: 1-3ms (SQLite FTS5, pre-built index)
- First-ever search: ~13s (builds FTS5 DB + JSON cache, persists in %TEMP%)
- Subsequent server restarts: ~0.2s (loads from cached DB)
